@page "/privacy"
@attribute [Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authorization.AllowAnonymous]
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy - Family Kitchen";
}
<div class="prose">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="muted small">Last updated: January 25, 2026</p>

    <h2>What We Collect</h2>
    <p>Family Kitchen collects minimal information needed to provide our service:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Email address</strong> — Used for authentication and to identify your account</li>
        <li><strong>Display name and profile picture</strong> — From your Google account, shown to household members</li>
        <li><strong>Recipe and meal plan data</strong> — Content you create within the app</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>How We Use Your Data</h2>
    <p>
        Your data is used solely to provide the Family Kitchen service to you and your household members.
        We do not sell, share, or use your data for advertising purposes.
    </p>

    <h2>Data Storage</h2>
    <p>
        All data is stored on privately-owned servers. We do not use third-party cloud services for data
        storage. Your recipes, meal plans, and shopping lists remain under our direct control.
    </p>

    <h2>Data Deletion</h2>
    <p>
        You may request deletion of your account and all associated data at any time by contacting the
        household administrator.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>For privacy-related questions, please contact your household administrator.</p>

    <div class="mt"><a class="btn btn-outline" href="/dashboard">Back to Home</a></div>
</div>
